  "texts": [
    "We review now a series of tools aimed at responsible foresight (some of the tools taking inspiration from the ones listed in GESDA (2024)), and discuss the role of computational modeling in each of those, presenting recent and novel examples from the literature.",
    "While anticipating the future is challenging, it is possible to achieve valuable insights, as demonstrated by approaches like superforecasting and prediction markets.",
    "These methods synthesize various data sources to produce meaningful forecasts.",
    "Superforecasting (Tetlock and Gardner; 2016), a skill typically honed by individuals (but extendable also to computational methods/agents) known for their consistent accuracy in making probabilistic predictions, demonstrates that certain methods and cognitive strategies can enhance the ability to forecast uncertain events (e.g.",
    "disciplined reasoning, openness to updating beliefs, and careful consideration of probabilities)."
  ],
